# Normalize all text files to LF on checkout/checkin. CRLF is fatal here:
#  - Rust sources fail the cross build (AGENTS.md: LF required, CRLF breaks build)
#  - The installer (install-usb.ps1) emits device-side shell scripts (run.sh,
#    deploy.sh) via literal here-strings; a CRLF copy produces a CRLF run.sh,
#    whose "#!/bin/sh\r" shebang busybox cannot exec -> the KoThok launch hook
#    silently fails. Force LF so Windows checkouts (core.autocrlf=true) cannot
#    reintroduce CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit overrides for the deploy-critical and source paths.
*.ps1 text eol=lf
*.sh  text eol=lf
*.rs  text eol=lf
*.slint text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf

# Generated/binary artifacts: never normalize or diff.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.mp3 binary
*.epub binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
